Cambodia is included in WHO's Western Pacific Region (http://apps.who.int/gho/data/node.country.regionWPR?lang=en). Cambodia, with a population of over 14.8 million, is located in the southern portion of the Indochina Peninsula in Southeast Asia (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cambodia). The capital and largest city is Phnom Penh. For a map of Cambodia's 23 provinces and Phnom Penh special administrative area, see http://ephotopix.com/image/asia/cambodia_province_map.gif. - Mod.ML

